  "description": [
    "Friday September 11 1942 A Year of War for Russian Jewry Copyright 1942 Jewish Telegraphic Agency Inc EDITORS NOTE In this article prepared by Dr Segal for the American Jewish Year Book he surveys the changes that war has brought for the Jews of Russia in ternally and in their relations with the Jews of the world The first year of the Nazi Soviet war brought about radical changes in the life of the Jews in the Soviet Union The impact of the war against Hitlerism the great enemy not only of Russia hut also of the Jewish people seems to have produced among the Jews of the Soviet Union the realization of their solidarity of fate with that of the democratic world and especially of the Jew ish people throughout the world Also the geographical distribution of Soviet Jewry has been consid erably altered Hundreds of thousands of Jews from the Baltic and Ukrainian provinces were evacuated by the Russian army before the on slought of the Nazis However the territory that the Nazis have succeeded in occupying during the first year of their war against Soviet Russia is one of the most densely populated by Jews In 1941"
  ],
